<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP20_AdventureAwaits_CustomVenues" s="481193">
  <T n="category">481599<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_AdventureAwaits--></T>
  <T n="name">0xA9FFA3D1<!--String: "Custom Venues"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_CustomVenues_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:9e9e0584a4e4971e</T>
      <T n="text">0x89CC70CD<!--String: "Ever dreamed of making a venue that feels completely like your own? That's where <font color="#199C2C"><b>Custom Venues</b></font> come in!\n\nUnlike standard venue lot types like Bars or Gyms, Custom Venues give you the freedom to decide exactly what kind of activities should happen, which Sims should show up, and what the vibe is.\n\nWant a lakeside retreat with early morning kayak sessions and late-night Stargazing on the dock? You can build that. Or maybe a laid-back forest hangout spot where Sims roast marshmallows and swap stories by the fire? That too. With Custom Venues, the rules are yours to write!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_CustomVenues_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:9e9e0584a4e4971d</T>
      <T n="text">0xE88F9775<!--String: "To convert an existing lot type into a Custom Venue, start by entering Manage Worlds from either Live Mode or Main Menu. Select the lot you'd like to convert and enter Build Mode.\n\nOnce you have entered Build Mode, select <font color="#199C2C"><b>Venue Info</b></font>, then open the Lot Type dropdown menu and convert the lot to a <font color="#199C2C"><b>Custom Venue</b></font>. After the lot has been successfully converted, a new button will appear that lets you <font color="#199C2C"><b>Configure Schedule Preset</b></font>!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_CustomVenues_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:9e9e0584a4e4971c</T>
      <T n="text">0xDA8B75DF<!--String: "When setting up a Custom Venue, you don't have to start from scratch. You'll have access to three premade Schedule Presets: <font color="#199C2C"><b>Outdoor Kids Camp</b></font>, <font color="#199C2C"><b>Romantic Competition</b></font>, and <font color="#199C2C"><b>Fitness Retreat</b></font>.\n\nThese Schedule Presets are ready to be applied to any Custom Venue lot. In addition to these, there are also a variety of other themed templates that offer a strong starting point for different kinds of Custom Venues. They're great for jumping in fast or as a foundation for your own ideas!\n\nYou can also build your own from the ground up. Just open the Preset dropdown and select <font color="#199C2C"><b>Create New</b></font> to start crafting a brand-new schedule. This gives you full control over roles, activities, time blocks, outfits, and behaviors. Everything needed to bring your unique vision to life!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_CustomVenues_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:9e9e0584a4e4971b</T>
      <T n="text">0xAA1566A8<!--String: "Now you're ready to create a <font color="#199C2C"><b>Schedule Preset</b></font> for your Custom Venue! A Schedule Preset defines what happens throughout the day, what type of Sims show up, what they wear, and what activities they will engage in!\n\nWhen editing a Schedule Preset, you'll set the <font color="#199C2C"><b>timeslots</b></font> that make up the venue's daily schedule. For each timeslot, you can assign specific activities and determine which roles are required to make it happen. For example, you might start your schedule at a 9 AM timeslot where guests head out for a morning kayak session while the Retreat Leader tends the bar. Then the next timeslot might start at 12 PM for a lunchtime activity!\n\nOnce your schedule and roles are in place, select confirm and the Custom Venue will follow your Schedule Preset every time you visit the lot!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_CustomVenues_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:9e9e0584a4e4971a</T>
      <T n="text">0xF63B0E23<!--String: "While you can't assign specific Sims to roles directly from Manage Worlds, you can do it once you're actively visiting the Custom Venue with a household Sim. Travel to the Custom Venue lot with a household Sim, and you'll be able to assign any known Sims including friends or neighbors into roles you've defined. This gives you the flexibility to cast familiar Sims into key positions like Instructor, Host, or Contestant while they're at the Custom Venue!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_CustomVenues_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:9e9e0584a4e49719</T>
      <T n="text">0x626902BE<!--String: "Any Custom Venues with a Schedule Preset applied will carry over into the Getaway Planner! That means you won't have to rebuild the schedule from scratch when planning your Getaway, it's already linked and ready to go.\n\nThis makes Custom Venues ideal for hosting repeatable or highly tailored Getaways. When entering the Locations tab of the Getaway planner, the Custom Venue lot will have the Schedule Preset ready for you in the Schedules tab!"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
